Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back. And how was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, was just a salaried employee\Nthat gave in to his temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.78,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to do with the syndicate;\Nthey just wanted money to play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.41,0:02:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they were just thugs!\NThey went to the cops penniless!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.12,0:02:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of you caught the criminals, but no\Nclue about the bounty we're really after?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They still use paper just\Nfor all the complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.49,0:03:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, they're just harassing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And{\i0}, it's a waste of valuable resources!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.07,0:03:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The e-mail server is going down\Nfrom the sheer number of complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a movement out there\Nto sue our company for damages...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.00,0:03:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are the\Nbounty hunters doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We already have a huge bounty on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, however...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.51,0:03:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Amigo{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you bounty hunters in the\NSol system, how are y'all doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.47,0:03:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once again, it's time for {\i1}Big Shot{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start with today's hot news!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.10,0:03:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They apprehended the culprit in\Nthe series of recent gate assaults!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.27,0:03:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? The bounty on him was\N12 million woolongs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the weird thing is that\N20 culprits were apprehended!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.53,0:03:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they were all caught in\Nthe act, but none were the mastermind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you don't get the reward\Nunless you find that mastermind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.41,0:03:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.66,0:03:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sorry for all the guys\Nwho caught the culprits!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:04:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell do these\Nthugs that normally just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.92,0:04:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rob convenience stores attack the gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.05,0:04:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there are fads in crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, "Hyperspace gates are the {\i1}in {\i0}thing\Namong today's fashion-conscious kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That girl won't even look your way until
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you assault at least\None gate!" or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we trade the\Ninformation that we each have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.28,0:04:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And split the bounty three ways...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one that started all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,saying that we should\Nresearch this case on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You also said that the occasional rivalry\Nbetween comrades would be good for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, did the reward amount\Nmake you lose your memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You guys were\Nreally keen on the idea, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we all wanted\Nthe bounty to ourselves, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, all 20 cases\Nwere done the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them infiltrated the tollbooth...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...deftly attached the hacking unit...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.81,0:05:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and in the exact moment that passing\Nships access the tollbooth to pay the toll,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they stole the entire balance\Nfrom the credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.36,0:05:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the unit automatically\Nsent the money data that it just stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It immediately laundered all\Nthe funds in a bank on Europa,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,making it impossible\Nto track where it went.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the culprits that were caught\Nin the act have nothing in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:06:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Age, gender, nationality,\Nreligion, criminal record...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of it, nobody has any of\Nthe money that they supposedly stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's about all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy that I nabbed said\Nthat he was just following
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the instructions from a manual\Nthat he got through mail-order.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps the other culprits are reading\Nthe same manual that he was?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manual?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.66,0:06:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A new criminal support software.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.57,0:06:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, it's a real bargain. For the low\Nintroductory price of 30,000 woolongs,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you too can be rich!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not easy to be a thief nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there are people who\Nwant manuals to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And where is this mail-order company?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a store that's only on the 'net,\Nso I don't know where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the store has already closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.18,0:06:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hacking unit that was placed\Non the gates was something that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,couldn't be made unless you knew\Nabout the gate system really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mastermind's likely someone who has\Nsome connection to the Gate Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.69,0:07:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my hunch, and I\Ninvestigated that front...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The programmers would be fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but the guys from the Gate Corporation\Nsuddenly became uncooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was as if they knew something,\Nbut didn't want us to find out about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:07:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess those are the\Nonly clues we have for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:08:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.21,0:08:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a memory cartridge for\Nplaying chess over the 'net.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This piece has one match in its memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, when you push it,\Nit connects to the 'net.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this has something\Nto do with this incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe all of this is a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, continue playing\Nthat game with the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.61,0:08:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go talk to the Gate\NCorporation guys once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.03,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lessee...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eenie, meenie, miney, moe...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.87,0:08:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Play ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another bounty hunter?\NI don't care, send him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's asking about a\Nchess-loving programmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.28,0:09:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, Jonathan, were you another one that\Nwent through all the trouble to get nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This thing isn't that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.17,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we have given\Nout all the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What more are you saying\Nyou would like to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but there is no smoking\Nallowed in this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops. I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually I had something\Nthat I wanted you to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:10:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a planned game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.37,0:10:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys at the Gate Corporation\Nshould know what this means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, to put a bounty on a mastermind\Nthat we aren't even sure exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.67,0:10:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...suggests that it's someone you don't\Nwant the police to know about, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bounty hunters should just\Nlook for their bounties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who you are,\Nand whether or not you used to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.27,0:10:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,work for the ISSP, but it's better for\Nyou to not make any extra inquiries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.10,0:10:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going home. Make sure he\Nis kindly escorted out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.11,0:10:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn this old piece of shit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe our risk is too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that gets out to the general public...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.29,0:10:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am fully aware of our risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't catch him,\Nthe situation will just get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.25,0:10:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why is a ghost from 50 years\Nago coming back now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:11:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he gave\Neveryone a chess piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chessmaster Hex...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it {\i1}is {\i0}a game that he set up...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chessmaster Hex...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good. This doesn't have\Nanything other than chess data in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what they were\Ngoing to do with such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is no meaning to the content,\Nmaybe the pieces are the message...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:11:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, great!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, I have a name...\NCan you investigate the guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might be the mastermind\Nbehind this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ed's really busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checkmate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.93,0:12:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or so you thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.68,0:12:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fork the king and the rook!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed! This is either an idiot or a genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like this chap...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.91,0:12:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chessmaster Hex.\NEstimated to be 98 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A programmer that had been\Ndubbed a genius from his teens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Cosmo-net chess tournaments, he\Ndominated the champion's seat for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He began work on the Hyperspace Gate\NControl Program when he was 30...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.05,0:13:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and created the central control system\Nthat all gates use to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that was his fatal error.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.27,0:13:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He started to doubt the safety\Nof the gates he helped create
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was against putting\Nthem to practical use.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.61,0:13:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, he was banned\Nfrom the Gate Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, his whereabouts have\Nbeen unknown for 50 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's the mastermind behind\Nour current string of crimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.74,0:13:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, why is he seeking\Nrevenge 50 years after the fact?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we figure out where he is,\Nwe'll know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ed's really busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.67,0:13:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you, quit playing games\Nso much and help out a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ed, we want to figure out\Nwhere a guy named Hex is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.30,0:13:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hex... Hex... The Chessmaster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's who I'm playing\Nchess against right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost at the location we got from\Nthe trace we did on Ed's chess opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys standing by?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he's basically\Ngiving us his exact location...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.71,0:14:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we even trust that\Ntrace in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.55,0:14:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ya think he'd be in a dump like this?\N--No, I think it was... that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.72,0:14:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had heard once that there was a place\Nwhere all the scrapped remains of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.10,0:14:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,obsolete gates were gathered along with\Nscrap metal and abandoned spaceships...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.27,0:14:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and that there were people\Nthat started living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.19,0:14:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell do they want\Nto live here of all places?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That area has no nationality,\Nnor a government.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to pay taxes,\Nand there are no cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.57,0:14:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... It's the perfect\Nplace to hide yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.05,0:15:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.55,0:15:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This might be the continuation of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever happens, happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we have air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.03,0:16:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then there is someone here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jonathan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for leading the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.54,0:16:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... were following us the whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tough luck for you, but I have\Nimportant business with that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll be going ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.80,0:17:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.19,0:17:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.58,0:17:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peace to the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and love to my bank account!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.48,0:18:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chessmaster Hex?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.30,0:18:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you be a little quieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't joke with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.85,0:18:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away with\Npretending to be senile!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.31,0:18:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are {\i1}you{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hand over\Nthe money you stole,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll get a nice hole in your brain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a big tube you got there...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, whatcha doin', Hex?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.99,0:19:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta hear this. It's my first\Nformidable opponent in quite a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must be some player if\Nyou have trouble winning!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.12,0:19:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that, where's lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are ya saying?\NYou just ate lunch a while back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really, you've lost so much of yer mind\N--Who are these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.21,0:19:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--that all you can do is play chess!\N--Dunno. But you know, this old fogey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.22,0:19:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Have ya lost it?\N--Like you can speak... You...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To... To think my life savings\Nare never coming back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn... Goddammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone and everyone,\Nyou and that guy over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.10,0:19:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is all a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.54,0:19:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we gonna do?\NThis old man doesn't seem to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.50,0:19:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remember anything about yesterday,\Nlet alone 50 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.13,0:19:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.63,0:19:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hex is no longer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.80,0:20:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we merely have an\Nold man that loves games...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.68,0:20:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, Hex was riled up for\Nrevenge, and planned this all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made it so that this incident\Nwould happen 50 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,during the one moment that the\NGate Program gets automatically updated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even making those that\Nphysically commit the crime
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hold chess pieces to hint\Nthat it was his doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, to that old-timer,\N50 years was too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.41,0:20:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went senile, and had\Ncompletely forgotten
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.41,0:20:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about the traps that he himself had set.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it works out better for you this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.17,0:20:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because now you don't\Nhave to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.13,0:20:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fundamental defect\Nin the gates leaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, the price you paid was\Nthat {\i1}we {\i0}learned about that defect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want? Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or... are you planning to leak\Nthis information to the press?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave that old guy alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.95,0:21:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.28,0:21:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good deal, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ed would get lonely if she\Nlost her chess partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're playing that thing again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not again. Still.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been playing that\Nthing this whole {\i1}week{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.27,0:21:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.81,0:21:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.35,0:21:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, newcomer. You seem happy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.32,0:21:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a really easygoing fellow, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.78,0:21:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.04,0:22:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Too much time has passed by...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.72,0:22:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...to lament that we were deeply in love.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.02,0:23:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wind keeps blowing, while my heart...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...cannot heal all the tears in it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone, cry for me with parched eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The real folk blues.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.58,0:23:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I only want to know what true sadness is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.05,0:23:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sitting in muddy water...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...isn't such a bad life...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.19,0:23:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...if it ends after the first time...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.08,0:24:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love... It is to believe everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.66,0:24:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.87,0:24:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love... It is the heart that provides for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.09,0:24:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on... Was that what\Nthe story was about?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.76,0:24:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love... It is the heart\Nthat accepts everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.22,0:24:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, this is getting fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.46,0:24:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whitney... You loved me that much...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.28,0:24:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really can't trust\Nthe previews on this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.80,0:24:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A romantic love story for all you lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.53,0:24:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: "My Funny Valentine."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.10,0:24:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.95,0:24:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a lie. A lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.74,0:24:36.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"My Funny Valentine"
